modules.description: Checks for overlapping memory regions between two bigarrays, returning the length of the overlap and the starting indices in each array. Operates on bigarrays with identical element types and dimensions. Used to extract a shared segment from two arrays into a new bigarray for direct manipulation.

Computes overlapping regions between multi-dimensional arrays, returning coordinates and dimensions of shared elements. Handles various array types including 0D, 1D, 2D, and 3D structures with precise indexing. Determines if two zero-dimensional arrays are identical and identifies overlapping subarrays in higher dimensions.
